        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 2:40PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 239 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Cassopolis to 9 miles
west of Constantine. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Three Rivers, Constantine, Cassopolis, Centreville, Colon, Nottawa,
Penn, Vandalia, Dailey, Paradise Lake, Calvin Center, Donnell Lake,
Fishers Lake, Fairfax, Jones, Diamond Lake, Corey Lake, Shavehead
Lake, Wasepi, and Clear Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
